# ─── IMPORTANT: Use POOLED connection string for DATABASE_URL ──────────────────
#
# Neon provides TWO connection strings in your dashboard:
#
#   1. Pooled (PgBouncer)  → use this for DATABASE_URL
#      Looks like: postgresql://user:pass@ep-xxx.pooler.neon.tech/dbname?pgbouncer=true&sslmode=require
#
#   2. Direct              → use this for DIRECT_URL (migrations only)
#      Looks like: postgresql://user:pass@ep-xxx.neon.tech/dbname?sslmode=require
#
# Using the POOLED URL eliminates the ~800-2000ms SSL/TCP cold-start time
# because PgBouncer maintains a persistent pool of connections to Postgres.
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# HOW TO GET IT:
#   1. Open dashboard.neon.tech → your project → "Connection Details"
#   2. Select "Connection pooling" checkbox → copy the URL
#   3. Paste it below as DATABASE_URL, appending: ?pgbouncer=true&connection_limit=1
#      (connection_limit=1 is recommended for serverless environments)
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# DATABASE_URL="postgresql://user:pass@ep-xxx.pooler.neon.tech/dbname?pgbouncer=true&sslmode=require&connection_limit=1"
# DIRECT_URL="postgresql://user:pass@ep-xxx.neon.tech/dbname?sslmode=require"

# Clerk
# NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=pk_...
# CLERK_SECRET_KEY=sk_...

# App
# NEXT_PUBLIC_CURRENCY_SYMBOL=$

# Admin (optional — if not set, any signed-in user can access /admin)
# NEXT_PUBLIC_ADMIN_USER_ID=user_xxxx
